    <title>Page Structure: Rules of thumb for a web page</title>
    <contents>
      <h2>Title</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Describes content on specific page.</li>
        <li>Name of the Website .</li>
      </ol>
      <h2>Landmarks</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Typical landmark usage:
          <ul>
            <li>1 Banner</li>
            <li>1 Main</li>
            <li>1 or more navigation</li>
            <li>1 Contentinfo</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>The longer the list the more time need to read and decide.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Headings</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><code>h1</code> heading used to identify the start of the main content.</li>
